<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-7B8634B6-A3A4-4DAA-BF9D-10586F2D4E53" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-7B8634B6-A3A4-4DAA-BF9D-10586F2D4E53" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">How to enter Zero SDS</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M125150-B44"><p class="- topic/p ">You need Zero SDS when the system refuses to start normally. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">SDS</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="M140690-B27" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph ">Purpose</ph></title><p class="- topic/p ">In Zero SDS none of the usual engine initializations take place and the heaters remain OFF. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Through the Zero SDS interface, you can start various SDS tests on the system to find the problem. 
</p></section><section id="SECTION_E3FB64D8D61A42D78A552DAA36089786" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Procedure to start Zero SDS</title><ol id="OL_A8C9FCBBBE844C71B7BB75E2B4233EF5" class="- topic/ol "><li id="LI_411C23D8589C4ACD9EE6D9ABDEB17D11" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Insert the SAM Key with a valid license in the USB connection below the User Interface. 
</p></li><li id="LI_1AF75BE527DC4BE8BAFD0482006A9280" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Use the On/off button to (re-)start the system.
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">In the boot screen on the printer operator panel tap on the service icon as indicated below. 
</p><fig id="FIG_9ABED61E9C52448B8DFF7AEC3CB96269" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5CAFE6D0-3C0E-4BCC-AC6D-97044B776B80-low.png" id="IMAGE_106042A3E5E5421CA14F2C041ABCA4A4" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5CAFE6D0-3C0E-4BCC-AC6D-97044B776B80-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">As soon as the software is ready Adam will start. 
</p><fig id="GUID-909DE7ED-ECFF-4D72-B3CA-86DD13DEC877" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-B6668541-64AB-4653-830A-F31F115D8B85-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B6668541-64AB-4653-830A-F31F115D8B85-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">As soon as Adam is ready tap the SDS button. 
</p><fig id="GUID-32D5E12B-EADF-43CB-9E5A-A8199A4C353D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F0540FA2-3FAD-4386-A289-4FBAEFCBB336-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F0540FA2-3FAD-4386-A289-4FBAEFCBB336-low.png"/></fig></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">You are in Zero SDS now. 
</p></li></ol></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-45686CBD-5197-47D8-B84A-01B685BBD817.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>SDS</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
